Real Madrid beat Valencia on penalties in the Spanish Super Cup semi-finals at the King Fahd Stadium in Saudi Arabia. Karim Benzema’s penalty put the European and La Liga champions ahead but Samuel Lino levelled just after half-time to make it 1-1 in Riyadh. READ MORE: La-liga: Real Madrid Miss Chance To Leap-Frog Barcelona After Loss To Villareal “Obviously as a goalkeeper you have to study penalties,” Courtois said. “Gaya missed his last one against Sevilla on the left, and scored his last one down the middle against Betis, so we knew he was going to shoot there.” 